<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Tigran Liloyan] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan 16 May TASS -- Armenian President Levon 
Ter-Petrosyan expressed condolences to the families of the 
victims of the bomb explosion in the Armenian drama theater in 
Tbilisi on Sunday [15 May] that wounded 16 people. 
  Ter-Petrosyan denounced the action as a "dreadful 
terroristic 
act" and a "provocation against traditional Armenian-Georgian 
friendship." 
  The Armenian leader expressed the confidence that the 
accident will not affect relations between the two nations and 
that the Georgian authorities will take all necessary measures 
to find and punish the terrorists and prevent terroristic acts 
against the Armenians living in Georgia. 

